---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title='Plasterers & Painters in Uxbridge | Hancock' description='Plastering and painting in Uxbridge. Fixed-price quotes from City & Guilds certified contractors covering Uxbridge and the surrounding area.' activePage='areas'>
<section style="position:relative;height:380px;display:flex;align-items:flex-end;">
  <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;background-image:url('/uploads/Hancock-plastering-and-painting%20(13).webp');background-size:cover;background-position:center 30%;"></div>
  <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;background:linear-gradient(to top,rgba(15,23,42,0.9) 0%,rgba(15,23,42,0.45) 60%,rgba(15,23,42,0.15) 100%);"></div>
  <div style="position:relative;z-index:1;max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px 52px;width:100%;box-sizing:border-box;">
    <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);margin:0 0 12px;"><a href="/" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);text-decoration:none;">Home</a> / <a href="/areas" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);text-decoration:none;">Areas</a> / Uxbridge</p>
    <h1 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(34px,5vw,58px);font-weight:700;color:#ffffff;margin:0 0 12px;letter-spacing:-0.04em;line-height:1.05;">Plasterer in Uxbridge</h1>
    <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:17px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.75);margin:0;">UB8/UB10 · Plastering, rendering &amp; commercial decorating across Uxbridge.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:64px 24px;background:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;gap:64px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <div style="flex:2;min-width:280px;">
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#11ADE2;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">About this area</p>
      <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,32px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 20px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">Uxbridge mixes commercial buildings with established residential streets.</h2>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 16px;">Uxbridge town centre is predominantly commercial with substantial 1960s–80s office and retail stock. The residential areas branch out into Hillingdon, Cowley, and Uxbridge Moor — a mix of Victorian workers' terraces, interwar semis, and newer development around the tube station corridor.</p>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">The commercial sector generates consistent demand for decorating during lease renewals, office fit-outs, and property refreshes. The residential streets around Belmont Road and the older parts of town generate the domestic plastering and repair work.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="flex:1;min-width:220px;">
      <div style="background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;">
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:#64748B;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;margin:0 0 16px;">Area facts</p>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;">
          <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;padding-bottom:10px;"><span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:#64748B;">Postcode</span><span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;">UB8 / UB10</span></div>
          <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;padding-bottom:10px;"><span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:#64748B;">Dominant era</span><span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;">Mixed / commercial</span></div>
          <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;"><span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:13px;color:#64748B;">From Harefield</span><span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;">~10 mins</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:64px 24px;background:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;gap:64px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <div style="flex:1;min-width:300px;">
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#11ADE2;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">Neighbourhoods we work in</p>
      <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,30px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 20px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">A commercial town centre with residential on every side.</h2>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 16px;">Uxbridge is the administrative heart of Hillingdon — a busy commercial centre with offices, retail, and the Brunel University campus, ringed by residential neighbourhoods of very different ages. <strong>Cowley and Yiewsley</strong> hold older terraced and interwar housing; <strong>Hillingdon</strong> runs from Victorian through 1930s semis to postwar estates; and the <strong>St Andrew's Park</strong> development on the former RAF Uxbridge site has added a large pocket of modern new-build apartments and houses.</p>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 16px;">That spread means we move between two kinds of work in Uxbridge — domestic plastering and decorating on the residential streets, and commercial decorating for the offices, lettings, and retail units around the town centre and the Chimes.</p>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">The Grand Union Canal threads through the area, and a number of older properties near the water and the town centre are solid-brick Victorian — no cavity, higher damp risk, and plaster that needs the right diagnosis before it's patched.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="flex:1;min-width:300px;">
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#11ADE2;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">What clients ask for</p>
      <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,30px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 20px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">Domestic refits and commercial turnarounds.</h2>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 16px;">On the residential side it's the usual settled-suburb mix: re-skims after kitchen and bathroom refits, plastering out extensions, ceiling work, and crack repairs on the older stock. The commercial side is where Uxbridge differs from our quieter areas — office repaints between tenancies, retail unit fit-outs, and decorating turnarounds on lettings, often needed to a tight, fixed deadline.</p>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 16px;">Commercial work frequently means evening or weekend access to avoid disrupting trading — we'll plan around your hours and agree the timeline up front, in writing.</p>
      <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:16px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">Whether it's a homeowner or a managing agent, the principle is the same: a fixed price agreed before we start, and the same person on the tools who quoted the job.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#F8FAFC;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#11ADE2;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 24px;">Working in Uxbridge</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(220px,1fr));gap:20px;">
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">~15 minutes from base</h3>
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">An easy run from Harefield down the A4020 or via the A40. Uxbridge is a regular working area, domestic and commercial — no travel premium on the quote.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Access &amp; parking</h3>
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Suburban streets are simple; the town-centre commercial sites need access planned around loading bays and trading hours. Tell us the constraints and we'll work to them.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Domestic &amp; commercial</h3>
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">From a single room in a Hillingdon semi to a multi-office repaint between tenancies. We scale the approach and the schedule to the job.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Clean, tidy, insured</h3>
        <p style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Surfaces protected, site left tidy daily, minimal disruption to home or business. Fully insured, City &amp; Guilds qualified, no subcontractors.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:0;">
  <div style="position:relative;height:clamp(300px,42vw,440px);">
    <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background-image:url('/uploads/Hancock-plastering-and-painting%20(8).webp');background-size:cover;background-position:center;"></div>
